 this controversial and often misunderstood industry, Price-Glynn draws a fascinating portrait of life and work inside the strip club.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPower (Social sciences)vCase studies. 0aSex rolevCase studies. 0aSex-oriented businessesxSocial aspectszUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aStripteaserszUnited StatesvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aLions.  aPrice-Glynn.  aabout.  aaccess.  aagendas.  acocktail.  acompeting.  aconflict-ridden.  adeep.  aeconomic.  afourteen.  afueled.  aideas.  ainterests.  alabor.  amen.  amonths.  arace.  areveals.  asexuality.  aspent.  astereotypical.  auncommonly.  avalue.  awaitress.  awomen.  aworking.  aworkplace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081476760340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814768532.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814768532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814768532/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK